The paper deals with natural language understanding tasks and proposes deep neural network models for sequence chunking. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the arXiv category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper proposes new neural models for the task, which suggests that it may also belong to the categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper also mentions the use of these models for slot filling, which is a task related to natural language processing and may suggest that the paper belongs to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) category.
